section.section:
Standards to be used by the authority in reviewing and approving an eligible company and its economic development project shall include but not be limited to:
The creditworthiness of the eligible company;
The proposed capital investment to be made;
The number of new full-time jobs to be provided for the residents of the Commonwealth and the wages to be paid;
Support of the local community; and
The likelihood of the economic success of the economic development project.

text.section:
The application shall include but not be limited to:
The name of the applicant and identification of any affiliates of the applicant who will have some relation to the economic development project;
A description of the economic development project, including its location, the total investment in the economic development project, and total proposed eligible costs;
The projected number of new full-time jobs to be created as a result of the economic development project and identification of any affiliates who may employ persons hired to fill those jobs;
The number of existing full-time jobs at the site of the economic development project on the date of the application and a description and breakdown of the relevant affiliated employers;
Proposed wage and employee benefit amounts for the new full-time jobs to be created as a result of the proposed economic development project;
For proposed economic development projects new to the Commonwealth, certification by the eligible company that the economic development project could reasonably and efficiently locate outside of the Commonwealth and, without the incentives offered by the authority, the eligible company would likely locate outside the Commonwealth;
For eligible companies with an existing location in the Commonwealth considering an expansion, certification that the tax incentives are necessary for the expansion to occur;
A letter of support from a local governmental entity in the city or county where the economic development project will be located; and
Any other information the authority may require.
